# Quality Gates & Session Closure

Full workflow: [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](../../CONTRIBUTING.md) §9

## Before marking any task, batch, or file "complete"

Explicitly self-verify or prompt the author to confirm all **3 Local Quality Gates**:

| Gate | Check | Command / action |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 🟢 **1.1 Lint** | ESLint clean on changed files | `npm run lint` |
| 🟢 **1.2 Typecheck** | Strict TypeScript passes | `npm run typecheck` |
| 🟢 **1.3 Local Smoke** | `@smoke` suite in Docker (pre-push parity) | `npm run docker:test:smoke` |

Additional pre-commit requirements (Husky):

- Gate 1.1 **Cursor AI audit** against `docs/SELECTOR_POLICY.md` + no assertions in POMs (before `git commit`)

> 🛑 **Husky blocks:** Pre-commit rejects AI artifacts and unverified placeholders — including `// TODO: AI Generated`, `page.pause()`, and unverified stubs.
> ℹ️ **Emergency bypass:** `git push --no-verify` is reserved for exceptional cases only. Justification **must** be stated in the PR Escape Hatch section.

## Remote Gate 2

After push: GitHub Actions in Playwright Docker must pass before merge. Local Gate 1.3 does not replace CI.

## Meta-Prompt Evaluation (end of each batch PR)

Before opening a PR, run the evaluation prompt from `CONTRIBUTING.md` §9 and append results to [`docs/AI_VELOCITY_LOG.md`](../../docs/AI_VELOCITY_LOG.md).

**KPI targets:**

- Prompt-to-Code Ratio: **< 3 prompts per feature**
- Refactor Rate: **zero full-file rewrites** from poor context
- Context Efficiency: every prompt uses explicit `@file` references (`@CONTRIBUTING.md`, `@SELECTOR_POLICY.md`, source files)

## 🚫 Agent Constraints & Guardrails

- **Never** auto-commit or auto-push
- **Never** create files outside `docs/BLUEPRINT.md` structure
- **One batch per PR** — follow `docs/ROADMAP.md` sequentially
- Read `CONTRIBUTING.md` + `docs/SELECTOR_POLICY.md` before generating test or POM code
